1 Committee on Appropriations shall approve, amend, or deny any waiver recommended by
2 the board
3 A school district may request that the School Finance Accountability Board waive
4 any reduction to the district's state aid for general education, imposed under § 13-13-
5 73.5, or the penalty imposed upon a school district, pursuant to § 13-13-73.9.
6 The board may:
7 (1) Reduce a school district's state aid for general education, as provided in § 13-13-
8 73.5;
9 (2) Impose the penalty, as provided in § 13-13-73.9, upon a school district for failing
10 to comply with § 13-13-73.6 or 13-13-73.8;
11 (3) Require a review of the school district's accreditation if:
12 (a) The district's lowest general fund monthly cash balance exceeds the
13 district's allowable general fund cash balance; or
14 (b) The district has failed to comply with § 13-13-73.6 or 13-13-73.8; or
15 (4) Waive, in whole or in part:
16 (a) The reduction to a school district's state aid for general education required
17 under § 13-13-73.5, if the district demonstrates that the lowest monthly
18 general cash fund balance exceeded the allowable general fund cash
19 balance as the result of special circumstances; or
20 (b) A penalty imposed upon a school district by § 13-13-73.9, if the district
21 demonstrates that the district's failure to comply with § 13-13-73.6 or 13-
22 13-73.8 was the result of special circumstances.
23 The board may condition any waiver granted to a school district pursuant to
24 subsection (4)(a) upon the school district's annual lowest general fund monthly cash
25 balance equaling an amount less than the district's allowable general fund cash balance,
26 for at least three years. If the school district's lowest general fund monthly cash balance
27 exceeds the district's allowable general fund cash balance at any point during the three
28 years, the board may rescind the waiver and impose the penalty required under § 13-13-
29 73.5.
30 The board may condition any waiver granted to a school district pursuant to
31 subsection (4)(b) upon the school district increasing the district's average teacher
32 compensation in accordance with § 13-13-73.6 and paying each full-time equivalent
33 teacher a salary equal to the state minimum salary, as defined in § 13-13-73.8, for at
34 least three years. If a school district fails to increase the district's average teacher
35 compensation or fails to pay each full-time equivalent teacher a salary equal to the state
