1249A 3 1249
1 minimum salary at any point during the three years, the board may rescind the waiver
2 and impose the penalty required under § 13-13-73.9.
3 The School Finance Accountability Board shall promulgate rules, pursuant to
4 chapter 1-26, to establish the process by which a school district may request a waiver,
5 pursuant to this section, and the factors that the board may consider in granting a waiver
6 request from a school district. The factors must address the impact of employee
7 retirements on the district.
8 The Department of Education shall annually report to the Governor and the
9 Legislature the information collected pursuant to §§ 13-8-47 and 13-13-73.6.
10 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 1-45:
11 The School Finance Accountability Board shall promulgate rules, pursuant to
12 chapter 1-26, to establish:
13 (1) The process by which a school district may request a waiver, pursuant to § 13-13-
14 73.5 or 13-13-73.9;
15 (2) The documentation that a school district must present in order to demonstrate that
16 the district's failure to comply with § 13-13-73.5, 13-13-73.6, or 13-13-73.8 was
17 the result of special circumstances; and
18 (3) The factors that the board may use in determining whether a district's failure to
19 comply with § 13-13-73.5, 13-13-73.6, or 13-13-73.8 was the result of special
20 circumstances.
21 Any factors established by the board pursuant to subdivision (3) must include the
22 impact of the retirement of school district personnel on the district's general fund monthly
23 cash balance and average teacher salary.
24 Section 2. That § 13-13-73.5 be AMENDED:
25 13-13-73.5. Beginning on July 1, 2018, a If a school district's lowest general fund
26 monthly cash balance exceeds the district's allowable general fund cash balance, the
27 Department of Education shall reduce a school district's state aid for general education,
28 as calculated pursuant to § 13-13-73 shall be reduced, by subtracting an amount equal to
29 the difference of the district's allowable general fund cash balance subtracted from the
30 district's lowest general fund monthly cash balance. If the result difference is less than
31 zero, the reduction equals to the district's state aid for general education is zero.
